[Everlasting Torment](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Everlasting Torment) and [Forsaken Wastes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Forsaken Wastes) as mono-black-friendly variations on [Leyline of Punishment](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leyline of Punishment) and [Sulfuric Vortex](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sulfuric Vortex).  

You could also target yourself and use [Boon Reflection](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boon Reflection), [Sanguine Bond](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sanguine Bond), and [Tainted Sigil](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tainted Sigil)...as if the latter two aren't dangerous enough already.  

@Japicx: [Rain of Gore](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rain of Gore) would not work, since your opponent doesn't control [Laquatus's Champion](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Laquatus's Champion). Of course, you could use a [Bazaar Trader](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bazaar Trader) to "fix" that "problem." If you also run [Sulfuric Vortex](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sulfuric Vortex), you can make sure they can't gain the life back by killing it before you [Donate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Donate) it. (The combo will still work because you get to choose which replacement effect to use.)

